            <p class="text-big">
              Sound from a source such as a person speaking into a microphone or
              music from a sound system, is sent to an induction loop driver.
              The driver converts the audio into a magnetic signal, transmitted
              through a wire loop. This signal is picked up wirelessly by the
              <a href="#telecoil" class="teal-text">telecoil (T-Coil)</a> in a hearing
              aid or cochlear implant, which then converts it back into clear audio
              for the listener.
            </p>

