              Simply switching the hearing aid over to its ‘T setting’ will give
              the user access to broadcast audio signals in the looped area.
              Using a T-coil enabled device enables an audio signal to be picked
              up anywhere within a properly looped area, making it easy for
              people to move around and still hear clearly.
            </h5>
