            <h5>
              A hearing loop symbol should be mounted at eye level beside every
              entrance to a looped room, with an additional, larger sign
              positioned prominently on an internal wall. At reception desks or
              service counters, place the sign on, or immediately adjacent to,
              the counter in a spot that cannot be obscured by the person being
              served. For intercoms and help points, fix a small symbol beside
              the call button at a height that remains clearly visible to the
              user.
            </h5>

